title: IBHL Project: Japanese Culture Club App
description: An app coded for the International Baccalureate HL Computer Science Program with Java and SQLite designed to help the Japanese Culture Club schedule events and track attendance.

title: DS3 FA23 Workshop 3: Introduction to Backend
description: A workshop hosted by the Data Science Student Society to teach undergraduate students the fundamentals of backend development.

title: Rucio-SENSE DMM
description: Data Movement Manager (DMM) for the Rucio-SENSE interoperation prototype. DMM is the interface between Rucio (/FTS) and SENSE, making SDN operated HEP data-flows possible. Based on the relative priorities of the datasets we construct peer-to-peer private vlans with respective dedicated bandwidths to ensure we have accountability in the use of resources.

title: DS3 SP24 Workshop 4: Introduction to Flask
description: A workshop hosted by the Data Science Student Society illustrating the use of Flask to build personal websites.

title: Recipes Rating Classifier
description: A classifier designed to rate recipes based on their features. Done in collaboration with Emma Leung.

title: Bandwidth Allocation Testing
description: Repository for the research and testing of the bandwidth allocation algorithm for the Rucio-SENSE DMM.

title: COGS 108 Final Project: Gamification in Education
description: An exploration of the effects of gamified learning on standardized test scores. Done in collaboration with Hew Yeh, Kendall Underwood, Megha Kumar, and Jasmin Taylor.
